<font color="#FF0000">NO MORE PROTESTS....PLEASE!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jul 26 16:20:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Those who participated in that circus of death called war need to lay down their weapons, relax their vigilence, and calm their broken hearts.<br><br>
Those who protested with vicious attacks upon the legions of young men who simply obeyed the elected leadership, should stop their shouting long enough to realize that the shooting has stopped.<br><br>
Both, those who do not wish to see warfare again, for themselves and their children and those who do not wish to go through the rigors of protesting one more engagement, should carefully consider WHO and WHY they elect people to manage this nation's affairs.<br><br>
When the fight ends, it is not the time to stand around pointing fingers, making excuses, finding fault, bragging, complaining,rejoycing or crying...Instead, it is time for everyone to look around for those who are still bleeding.<br><br>
&quot;MY STUFF&quot;<br><br>
My soul is missing in action,<br>
my innocence was K.I.A.<br><br>
My heart is walking wounded,<br>
my dreams have lost their way.<br><br>
My mind is a prisoner of war,<br>
my lips have nothing to say&gt;<br><br>
My youth was deemed expendible,<br>
my feet have turned to clay.<br><br>
My thoughts are all in route-step,<br>
my feelings are in disarray.<br><br>
My future is at graves registration,<br>
my spirit held in sick-bay.<br><br>
My life's treaty has been broken,<br>
my outlook is dismal and gray.<br><br>
My dignity was marched to the gallows,<br>
when America threw me away.<br><br>
